description.plain: Katriana Sandra Huguet (born July 29, 1990), better known by her stage name Kat Dahlia (formerly Kat Hue), is a Cuban-American recording artist from Miami, Florida. Dahlia, a singer, songwriter and rapper, is known for her “razor sharp” lyrics and her “unique, aggressive flow”. She released her debut single “Gangsta”, in March 2013, to rave reviews. Dahlia released her debut studio album My Garden, in January 2015, with Vested in Culture and Epic Records, the latter of which she secured a recording contract with in 2012. In 2013, Dahlia ranked number eight on Billboard’s “Next Big Sound”.

songs.title: Gangsta

description.plain:
The chorus is a reference to 50 Cent’s 2002 hit single “Wanksta”. The theme of this song is how people claim to be “gangsta” without knowing what it really means.

A sample of “Wanksta” can be heard throughout the track (or more likely an interpolation from the piano notes of “Wanksta”).

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q--qBoAZwEk&list=UUg7lal8IC-xPyKfgH4rdUcA

songs.full_title: I Think I'm in Love by Kat Dahlia
songs.title: I Think I’m in Love

description.plain: I Think I’m in Love is the fifth song on the tracklist of Kat Dahlia’s debut studio album, My Garden, released in January, 2015. The song is about Dahlia’s reluctance to love a man she has met. This fits nicely into the narrative of the album, which was entirely based off a “toxic relationship” Dahlia was involved in.
